WEBVTT

00:09.885 --> 00:13.765
Come on. Come on. Should be
just enough to finish the job.

00:13.972 --> 00:16.646
Phew! Can't be too careful
with this stuff.

00:18.519 --> 00:20.066
(alarm sounding )

00:25.025 --> 00:25.742
( clock beeping )
"Warning."

00:25.943 --> 00:27.616
Blah blah blah...

00:27.819 --> 00:30.242
"Extreme usage could result
in minor gravity anomalies."

00:30.447 --> 00:32.448
Can it, Poindexter.
I've come this far.

00:32.658 --> 00:34.410
I'm not giving up now.

00:34.618 --> 00:35.870
( Blares )

00:38.997 --> 00:42.046
Yes, this is it!

00:44.795 --> 00:45.762
( Bleats )

01:02.271 --> 01:05.366
STAN: It's gonna be a bumpy ride,
but it'll all be worth it.

01:11.363 --> 01:13.036
Just eighteen more hours.

01:13.240 --> 01:15.868
Finally, everything changes...

01:16.076 --> 01:17.123
today.

01:35.012 --> 01:36.889
MABEL: Aah! It's here!
It's here! It's here!

01:37.097 --> 01:38.849
( Yawns )

01:39.057 --> 01:41.856
Okay, so I was just opening
random doors, because I'm a creep,

01:42.060 --> 01:44.483
when I found
something amazing!

01:44.688 --> 01:47.817
If it was worth waking up at
7:00 am for, that will be amazing.

01:48.025 --> 01:49.823
Feast your eyes!

01:50.027 --> 01:51.495
DIPPER: Whoa!

01:51.695 --> 01:53.868
Bro. Bro.
We're both thinkin' it.

01:54.072 --> 01:56.291
BOTH: Crazy rooftop
fireworks party!

01:56.491 --> 01:58.619
Not so fast, kids.

01:58.827 --> 02:03.207
There is no way on earth you're setting
off those dangerous, illegal fireworks...

02:03.415 --> 02:04.337
without me.

02:07.502 --> 02:08.970
(all laughing)

02:09.170 --> 02:10.592
Here you go, sweetie!

02:10.797 --> 02:13.425
Set something on fire for your
Grunkle Stan!

02:13.634 --> 02:15.932
I am the god
of destruction!

02:17.179 --> 02:19.932
ALL: ( laughing )
Whoa!

02:20.140 --> 02:22.518
<i>Ya“ Whoa'.!</i>

02:22.726 --> 02:24.399
Hold on a minute.
Do you have a permit for those?

02:24.561 --> 02:25.904
Uh...

02:26.104 --> 02:28.106
Uh, do you have a permit
for being totally lame?

02:28.315 --> 02:30.409
(all laughing)
Hey-o!

02:30.609 --> 02:33.408
( Chuckles )
Well, I can't argue with that.

02:33.612 --> 02:34.784
Carry on.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.786
Ha ha!
( sighs )

02:36.990 --> 02:39.118
But seriously, though, we should
probably clean this mess up.

02:41.995 --> 02:43.747
With water balloons?

02:43.955 --> 02:44.877
I don't see why not.

02:47.959 --> 02:48.881
Seriously?

02:49.086 --> 02:50.178
,,°,..".Z,'b!

02:50.379 --> 02:52.757
Ah, this is what
Saturdays are for.

02:52.923 --> 02:54.345
Doing dumb things forever!

02:54.549 --> 02:56.347
BOTH:
Dumb things forever!

02:56.551 --> 02:58.679
( laughing )
Whoa, there!

02:58.887 --> 02:59.683
To Grunkle Stan!

02:59.888 --> 03:02.266
Not just a great uncle--

03:02.474 --> 03:03.976
The greatest uncle!

03:04.184 --> 03:07.188
Ha ha. All right,
all right. I tell ya,

03:07.396 --> 03:10.775
it's unnatural for siblings to
get along as well as you do.

03:10.982 --> 03:13.405
Ha ha! Don't worry, we've still
got plenty of summer left

03:13.610 --> 03:14.907
to drive each other crazy.

03:15.112 --> 03:20.869
Heh...yeah...
plenty of summer left.

03:21.076 --> 03:24.171
Kids, there's something I, uh...
something I should tell you.

03:24.371 --> 03:27.375
It's, um... W-well, it's
complicated.

03:27.582 --> 03:29.175
I...

03:29.376 --> 03:31.845
I'm gonna go refresh my soda.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.513
Enjoy it while you can, Stan.

03:33.714 --> 03:35.512
They'll find out
sooner or later.

03:36.675 --> 03:38.677
Today's the day.

03:38.885 --> 03:39.977
What is that, a ladybug?

03:40.178 --> 03:41.896
( Grunting )

03:42.097 --> 03:43.474
What the--
Oh, no!

03:43.640 --> 03:44.562
(grunts)

03:45.976 --> 03:47.899
Target's secure.
Take the house.

03:49.521 --> 03:50.397
( Helicopters whirring )
What the...?

03:50.605 --> 03:51.447
Kids are secure.

03:51.648 --> 03:53.195
Roof team, go!

03:57.028 --> 03:58.871
Clear!

03:59.072 --> 04:00.574
Clear!

04:00.782 --> 04:01.783
( Squeals )

04:01.992 --> 04:04.165
Pig secure--we
have secured a pig.

04:06.496 --> 04:07.998
STAN:
( groaning )

04:08.165 --> 04:10.133
Hey, hands off, you stooge!

04:10.333 --> 04:11.880
Aah! I don't understand!

04:12.043 --> 04:15.297
What did I do that warrants
this much arresting?

04:16.923 --> 04:18.345
The government guys?

04:18.550 --> 04:20.392
I thought you
got eaten by zombies.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.141
We survived...barely.

04:22.345 --> 04:24.188
I used Trigger
as a human shield.

04:24.389 --> 04:25.857
He cried like a baby.

04:26.057 --> 04:26.853
Wha--hey!

04:27.058 --> 04:28.651
Not in front
of the special ops guys.

04:28.852 --> 04:31.856
This is security footage
of a government waste facility.

04:32.063 --> 04:36.284
At 0400 hours last night, someone robbed
300 gallons of dangerous waste.

04:36.443 --> 04:37.911
What? You think
that's me?

04:38.111 --> 04:39.784
Don't play dumb
with us, Pines!

04:39.988 --> 04:42.491
But I actually am dumb!
Last night I was restocking

04:42.699 --> 04:43.791
the gift shop...I swear!

04:43.992 --> 04:46.290
Wait, Grunkle Stan!

04:46.495 --> 04:48.964
You've got the wrong guy!
Our Grunkle Stan might shoplift

04:49.164 --> 04:52.885
the occasional tangerine,
but he's notsome evil supervillain.

04:53.084 --> 04:55.837
Listen, kid. We've been watching
your family all summer,

04:56.046 --> 04:57.719
and we've seen
some disturbing things,

04:57.881 --> 05:00.725
but nothing as dangerous
as what your uncle is hiding.

05:00.884 --> 05:03.888
Somewhere hidden in this
shack is a doomsday device!

05:05.889 --> 05:07.391
Trigger, you take
the children.

05:07.599 --> 05:10.352
I'll talk to the old man.
Sorry to break it to you, kids,

05:10.519 --> 05:12.692
but you don't know
your uncle at all.

05:14.231 --> 05:16.700
Icee pop, clear!
Hey!

05:23.907 --> 05:27.878
Kids! You gotta believe me!
For once I'm actually innocent!

05:28.078 --> 05:29.796
Kids!

05:29.996 --> 05:32.875
(siren wailing )

05:33.041 --> 05:35.544
♪ Headin' into work,
doot doo doo doo doo ♪

05:35.752 --> 05:37.004
Ground team,
move move move!

05:37.212 --> 05:38.179
Break down the door!

05:38.380 --> 05:40.098
Or...maybe not.

05:50.433 --> 05:53.733
Stanford Pines, you stand accused
of theft of government waste,

05:53.937 --> 05:56.565
conspiracy, and possession
of illegal weapons.

05:56.773 --> 05:58.366
How do you plead
to these charges?

05:58.567 --> 06:01.696
Uh..."guiltoccent."
I mean, "innoguilty."

06:01.903 --> 06:04.201
Um...can I
have my phone call?

06:06.491 --> 06:08.960
Okay, give me whatever you
got that comes with a free toy.

06:09.119 --> 06:10.666
( Radio static )
<i>Soos!</i>

06:10.871 --> 06:13.875
Mr. Pines? Is this some sort
of possession situation?

06:14.040 --> 06:14.757
<i>Soos, pick up!</i>

06:14.958 --> 06:16.084
Mr. Pines,
what happened?

06:16.293 --> 06:17.636
I heard you got arrested
or something?

06:17.836 --> 06:18.837
I had to go get
some panic food.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.672
<i>Listen, I need
something from you.</i>

06:20.839 --> 06:22.557
You know that vending machine
in the gift shop?

06:22.757 --> 06:24.851
<i>I need you to guard it
with your life.</i>

06:25.051 --> 06:26.894
<i>No matter what happens,
no matter who talks to you,</i>

06:27.095 --> 06:28.722
<i>don't let them touch
that machine!</i>

06:28.930 --> 06:30.898
( static, beeping )

06:31.099 --> 06:34.729
Time for a repair guy...
to become a repair man.

06:34.936 --> 06:37.485
Sir, your Junior Yum-Yum
Baby-Time Kiddo Meal?

06:37.689 --> 06:39.362
Just put one in my mouth.

06:42.652 --> 06:43.778
Let's do this.

06:49.492 --> 06:51.085
<i>We've got Mr. Pines
in custody.</i>

06:51.244 --> 06:52.962
<i>Our men are searching
the shack for that device.</i>

06:53.121 --> 06:55.249
<i>You take care
of those kids.</i>

06:55.457 --> 06:57.084
( gasps )
What are you gonna do to us?

06:57.292 --> 07:00.091
- We'll be taking you to child services.
- Boo!

07:00.295 --> 07:02.798
In the meantime, enjoy
some mindless reality TV...

07:02.964 --> 07:05.717
designed to pacify you and make
you stop asking questions.

07:05.926 --> 07:08.179
<i>I'm about to make
the incision.</i>

07:08.386 --> 07:10.184
<i>K er-prank!
Aah!</i>

07:10.388 --> 07:13.107
<i>You're watching Ker-Prank'd
with Justin Ker-Prank.</i>

07:13.308 --> 07:14.901
Dipper, this is crazy.

07:15.101 --> 07:17.195
There's no way Stan was
stealing hazardous waste.

07:17.395 --> 07:18.612
We gotta clear his name!

07:18.813 --> 07:19.735
Hmm...

07:21.942 --> 07:24.365
Wait a minute,
the security tapes!

07:24.569 --> 07:27.197
Didn't Stan say he was restocking
the gift shop last night?

07:27.364 --> 07:29.037
If we could get the Mystery Shack's
surveillance tapes,

07:29.199 --> 07:30.621
we could prove
he's innocent!

07:30.825 --> 07:33.920
We just need to think
of a way out of here.

07:34.079 --> 07:36.457
Think, Mabel. Think.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.552
( Tapping on window )
( squeaking on glass )

07:50.762 --> 07:52.935
( gasps )
No!

07:55.266 --> 07:56.142
Oh oh oh aah!

07:56.351 --> 07:57.477
Aah!
Aah!

07:57.686 --> 08:00.030
TRIGGER: Mayday, mayday!
Agent down!

08:02.941 --> 08:04.864
Uhh! Darn branch!

08:05.068 --> 08:07.366
H Uhh!
a ha: Yes!

08:07.570 --> 08:10.289
Backup! Requesting
backup! Aah!

08:12.659 --> 08:15.583
Come on, Dipper. We're gonna go
clear our uncle's name.

08:15.787 --> 08:18.666
Oh, you poor kids. You really think
your uncle's innocent?

08:18.873 --> 08:21.797
I've seen it all before.
False names, double lives.

08:21.960 --> 08:23.507
One minute, they're playing
with water balloons.

08:23.712 --> 08:25.680
The next, they're building
doomsday devices.

08:25.839 --> 08:27.841
Your uncle scammed
the whole world.

08:28.049 --> 08:29.301
You gonna let him
scam you, too?

08:31.011 --> 08:33.389
You--you don't know
what you're talking about.

08:33.596 --> 08:35.269
You're gonna regret this!

08:35.472 --> 08:36.690
( Airba 9 "em Aah! oys )

08:49.529 --> 08:51.873
Only five more hours
till it happens.

08:52.073 --> 08:53.700
I gotta be there!
Come on, Stan,

08:53.908 --> 08:54.875
you gotta think
of a way out of this.

08:55.076 --> 08:56.373
Think!
Think!

08:56.578 --> 08:58.251
( Watch alarm beeping )
Huh?

08:58.455 --> 09:00.708
( Alarm beeping )

09:05.879 --> 09:07.176
They're getting stronger!

09:07.380 --> 09:08.472
Of course, that's it!

09:10.467 --> 09:13.562
H-hey! Whoa!

09:13.720 --> 09:15.722
Is it just me, or did the entire
world just hiccup?

09:15.930 --> 09:18.399
I'm sure it's just
a baby-sized earthquake.

09:18.600 --> 09:20.648
Aww, baby-sized!

09:23.104 --> 09:25.106
It's happening!
The end times!

09:25.315 --> 09:28.535
When that machine activates,
I gotta get outta town!

09:28.735 --> 09:32.785
Git in there,
raccoon wife, git!

09:34.115 --> 09:35.958
Eh?
( panting )

09:36.159 --> 09:37.752
( panting )

09:37.952 --> 09:39.374
( police siren )

09:42.290 --> 09:43.667
MABEL: All right,
here's the plan.

09:43.875 --> 09:45.127
I'll take out
those two guard guys,

09:45.335 --> 09:47.303
you karate-chop the other dude
in the neck,

09:47.504 --> 09:49.302
and then we'll back-flip
through the front door!

09:49.506 --> 09:51.975
Mabel, aren't you forgetting
the simpler solution?

09:52.175 --> 09:53.097
On, right.

09:53.301 --> 09:55.144
So is it a rock,
or is it a face?

09:55.345 --> 09:57.814
I think...
it's a metaphor.

10:11.820 --> 10:13.117
All right.
If I was Stan,

10:13.279 --> 10:16.032
where would I hide
those surveillance tapes?

10:21.663 --> 10:23.791
Wait! The Antelabbit!

10:23.998 --> 10:25.124
Don't you mean
"jackalope"?

10:25.333 --> 10:26.926
Pfft!
That can't be right.

10:30.296 --> 10:31.673
Yes!
Yes!

10:31.840 --> 10:33.183
MABEL: It's this week!
This is it!

10:35.093 --> 10:37.642
<i>( Dance music playing ) Go!
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!</i>

10:37.846 --> 10:40.190
<i>Someone yelled "Wormy Dance."
We had to!</i>

10:40.390 --> 10:41.516
<i>Fast-forward.</i>

10:43.852 --> 10:46.776
DIPPER: Ha! There it is!
Stan restocking, like he said.

10:46.980 --> 10:48.527
And the date shows
it was last night!

10:48.731 --> 10:50.233
It's proof!
He's innocent!

10:57.240 --> 10:58.036
Uh-oh.

10:58.241 --> 11:00.790
Uh, maybe he's just going
to the bathroom outdoors,

11:00.994 --> 11:02.291
the way nature intended.

11:05.290 --> 11:07.042
( Qasps )

11:07.250 --> 11:09.753
DIPPER: Oh, no.
Stan, you didn't!

11:09.919 --> 11:12.763
Don't panic. That could be
anyone in that suit.

11:12.922 --> 11:15.675
<i>Aah! Hot Belgian waffles!</i>

11:15.884 --> 11:20.890
<i>Wait, I'm alone. I can swear
for real! Son-of-a--</i>

11:21.181 --> 11:22.854
That's him, all right.

11:23.057 --> 11:26.982
Okay, okay. So maybe Grunkle Stan
stole some toxic waste.

11:27.187 --> 11:29.986
That doesn't mean he's leading
a nefarious double life.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.568
Mabel,
I'm not so sure about that.

11:36.237 --> 11:38.660
What?
What is all this?

11:38.865 --> 11:40.742
Stetson Pinefield?

11:40.950 --> 11:44.454
Hal Forrester?
Andrew "8-Ball" Alcatraz?

11:44.662 --> 11:46.756
These are fake IDs, Mabel!

11:46.956 --> 11:49.209
You wouldn't need these unless you
were trying to hide your real identity.

11:49.417 --> 11:51.294
But why would Stan
do that?

11:58.927 --> 11:59.974
What?

12:00.178 --> 12:02.351
DIPPER: "Stan Pines Dead"?

12:02.555 --> 12:04.853
MABEL: "Foul play suspected
in Pines' death."

12:05.058 --> 12:08.779
"Fiery car crash,
brakes cut..." By who?

12:11.022 --> 12:13.741
DIPPER: "Unnamed grifter
at large"?

12:13.942 --> 12:15.694
Why would they call him
"unnamed"?

12:15.902 --> 12:17.745
Unless Stan...

12:17.946 --> 12:18.742
...isn't...

12:18.947 --> 12:20.790
"Stan?!
Stan?!

12:27.914 --> 12:29.461
DIPPER: Stan Pines is dead?

12:29.666 --> 12:31.339
Then who have we
been living with?

12:31.542 --> 12:32.714
It doesn't make
any sense!

12:32.919 --> 12:35.047
There has to be
some explanation.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.848
Maybe we're getting
Ker-Pranked!

12:37.048 --> 12:38.800
Justin Ker-Prank
is gonna jump up

12:39.008 --> 12:41.932
from behind one of these plants,
any minute now!

12:43.304 --> 12:45.602
Any minute, Justin.

12:45.807 --> 12:47.935
Can't believe it! This whole summer
I've beenlooking for answers,

12:48.142 --> 12:50.816
and the biggest mystery
was right under our nose.

12:51.020 --> 12:53.694
There's gotta be some kind
of explanation in here, somewhere.

12:53.898 --> 12:54.694
What the--?

12:54.899 --> 12:57.322
"Secret Code to Hideout"?

12:57.485 --> 12:59.237
Let me see that!

12:59.404 --> 13:01.782
A1, B, C3...

13:01.990 --> 13:03.833
I've never seen
a code like this.

13:04.033 --> 13:05.159
Wait, I have!

13:05.368 --> 13:07.621
Dipper,
it's the vending machine!

13:12.333 --> 13:14.552
All right, Pines.
Play time is over.

13:14.752 --> 13:16.880
Chopper's ready
to dust off to Washington.

13:17.088 --> 13:18.806
I'll enjoy
putting you away.

13:19.007 --> 13:21.556
What? Um, can't we stick
around for maybe one minute,

13:21.759 --> 13:23.727
uh, one minute,
thirty seconds?

13:23.928 --> 13:26.727
We're not falling
for your games, Pines.

13:26.931 --> 13:28.558
You've been running
your whole life.

13:28.725 --> 13:31.228
Your time is finally up.

13:31.436 --> 13:33.734
Bathroom break?
Just gimme 15 seconds.

13:33.938 --> 13:35.861
Sorry, but you've got
a flight to catch.

13:41.529 --> 13:42.781
Oh, yeah?
So do you!

13:42.989 --> 13:44.286
Huh?

13:44.490 --> 13:46.709
( Grunting )

13:49.954 --> 13:51.501
POWERS: Whoa, whoa, hey!

13:51.706 --> 13:53.333
Aah!

13:53.541 --> 13:54.542
( Grunting )

13:57.462 --> 14:00.762
POWERS: Hey!
Dang it, get back here!

14:00.923 --> 14:02.391
POWERS: Men, get him!

14:05.345 --> 14:08.599
POWERS: No! You won't get
away with this! Aah!

14:11.059 --> 14:13.187
_GOI1I1a get _Aah! Va!
