14:13.394 --> 14:15.396
POWERS: Ow!
( coffee mug breaks )

14:15.563 --> 14:17.691
Whoa!

14:17.899 --> 14:18.775
You know where
the Mystery Shack is?

14:18.983 --> 14:19.905
Uh, yeah.

14:20.109 --> 14:21.201
Okay,
here's a hundred bucks.

14:21.361 --> 14:22.908
Drive as far away
from the Shack as possible,

14:23.112 --> 14:25.581
and don't stop when the cops
start chasing you!

14:29.327 --> 14:31.204
POWERS: He's getting away!

14:31.412 --> 14:34.086
Obviously,
follow that cab!

14:36.376 --> 14:38.470
Stanford escaped!
He's at large!

14:38.669 --> 14:41.593
We need to sweep the town!
Move, move, move!

14:54.811 --> 14:56.108
All right, Soos,
remember the plan.

14:56.312 --> 14:57.814
Protect the machine,
earn Stan's trust,

14:58.022 --> 15:00.491
legally get adopted by Stan,
change name to Stan Junior.

15:00.691 --> 15:01.658
DIPPER: Soos!
Aah!

15:01.859 --> 15:03.202
Oh, kids,
where have you been?

15:03.361 --> 15:04.908
W-what are you doing here?

15:05.113 --> 15:06.911
Stan gave me a mission
to protect this machine.

15:07.115 --> 15:08.913
Ha! And I thought
I loved snacks!

15:09.117 --> 15:11.336
Soos, listen. Something huge
is going on here.

15:11.536 --> 15:13.334
If Stan is hiding
some dangerous secret,

15:13.538 --> 15:14.915
we need to find out
what it is!

15:15.081 --> 15:17.129
I need you
to step aside.

15:17.333 --> 15:21.383
Yeah, just let us through so we can prove
this is all just a big misunderstanding.

15:21.587 --> 15:25.512
Guys, I know this seems crazy, but I promised
Stan I would guard this with my life.

15:26.717 --> 15:28.970
I'm sorry, Soos.

15:29.178 --> 15:32.148
Aah! Attack glitter!
It's pretty, but it hurts!

15:32.348 --> 15:33.691
Please, Soos!
C'mon, Soos!

15:33.891 --> 15:35.893
Aw, c'mon, I don't wanna
fight you guys!

15:36.102 --> 15:38.150
This hurts me
more than it hurts you!

15:38.354 --> 15:39.901
( Grunting)
SOOS: Aah!

15:40.106 --> 15:42.484
Seriously, it hurts me
way more than it hurts you.

15:46.446 --> 15:48.915
ALL: Aah!

15:49.115 --> 15:51.959
ALL: ( coughing )

15:52.160 --> 15:52.956
Ohh...

15:53.119 --> 15:54.587
ALL: ( gasp )

15:59.125 --> 16:00.877
It's like something
from a video game.

16:01.043 --> 16:02.590
Or a dream.

16:02.795 --> 16:03.921
Or a nightmare.

16:08.384 --> 16:11.934
I gotta be there
when it happens! Aah!

16:17.018 --> 16:17.985
ALL: ( gasp )

16:21.355 --> 16:22.948
Guys, are we dreaming?
Somebody wake me up.

16:23.149 --> 16:24.867
This...can't be real.

16:25.067 --> 16:28.241
I don't understand. Why would
Mr. Pines have all this?

16:28.446 --> 16:30.665
It's just like
that bunker in the woods.

16:30.865 --> 16:33.084
But what is it doing
underneath the Mystery Shack?

16:33.242 --> 16:36.837
Okay, okay, so he's got a huge,
gigantic lab.

16:37.038 --> 16:38.756
That doesn't mean
anything bad.

16:38.956 --> 16:40.378
Everyone's got secrets!

16:41.709 --> 16:43.803
It's still Stan,
and he loves us.

16:43.961 --> 16:45.929
And we love him,
right?

16:46.130 --> 16:48.053
Can't be...
it's impossible.

16:48.257 --> 16:50.601
DIPPER: The other two journals?!

16:50.760 --> 16:53.604
All this time, all this time,
Stan had them!

16:53.763 --> 16:56.482
I can't believe it!
Was anything he said to us real?

16:56.641 --> 16:58.359
Why would he have
those journals?

16:58.559 --> 16:59.560
Maybe he's the author.

16:59.769 --> 17:01.612
Or maybe he stole them
from the author!

17:01.812 --> 17:03.814
Maybe the reason he has
all of those fake IDs

17:04.022 --> 17:05.695
is because he is
a master criminal,

17:05.900 --> 17:08.028
and this machine
is his master plan!

17:14.282 --> 17:15.329
Whoa!
( gasps )

17:17.912 --> 17:19.630
"I was wrong the whole time."

17:19.829 --> 17:22.709
"The machine was meant to create
knowledge, but it is too powerful!"

17:22.916 --> 17:24.839
"I was deceived,
and now it is too late!"

17:25.002 --> 17:26.628
"The device,
if fully operational,

17:26.837 --> 17:28.464
"could tear our universe apart!"

17:31.008 --> 17:33.010
"It must not fall
into the wrong hands.

17:33.219 --> 17:36.849
"If the clock ever reaches zero,
our universe is doomed."

17:39.100 --> 17:42.650
It's the final countdown!
Just like they always sung about!

17:46.023 --> 17:48.446
The agents were right!
We have to shut it down!

17:51.279 --> 17:52.872
ALL: ( gasp )

17:59.495 --> 18:00.872
There! Quick!

18:03.916 --> 18:05.463
Turn these! Together!

18:07.962 --> 18:09.680
That's it!
The shutdown switch!

18:12.925 --> 18:15.644
This all stops now!

18:15.803 --> 18:19.899
Don't touch that button!
( panting )

18:24.854 --> 18:25.946
Dipper, just back away.

18:27.857 --> 18:30.781
Please don't press that shutdown
button. You gotta trust me.

18:30.985 --> 18:32.282
And I should trust you, why?

18:32.486 --> 18:34.159
After you stole
radioactive waste,

18:34.322 --> 18:35.995
after you lied to us
all summer!

18:36.198 --> 18:37.916
I don't even know
who you are!

18:38.117 --> 18:39.539
Look, I know this
all seems nuts,

18:39.744 --> 18:41.166
but I need that machine
to stay on.

18:41.370 --> 18:42.747
If you just
let me explain--

18:42.955 --> 18:45.549
( watch beeping )
Oh! Oh, no! Brace yourselves!

18:46.959 --> 18:48.131
ALL: ( yelling )

18:53.966 --> 18:56.014
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

18:57.053 --> 18:58.020
Aah!

18:59.055 --> 19:00.932
ALL: ( yelling )

19:05.061 --> 19:06.813
COMPUTER: T-minus 35 seconds.

19:07.021 --> 19:08.864
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

19:09.065 --> 19:11.284
Whoa, aah!

19:11.442 --> 19:12.785
MABEL: Dipper!

19:13.944 --> 19:16.868
Mabel! Hurry!
Shut it down!

19:17.073 --> 19:19.246
( Grunting )

19:19.450 --> 19:21.452
[[511

19:21.661 --> 19:22.787
STAN: Mabel, Mabel, wait!

19:22.995 --> 19:24.372
5120p! Uhh!

19:24.580 --> 19:26.924
Soos, what are you doing?
I gave you an order!

19:27.083 --> 19:28.835
Sorry, Mr. Pines,
if that is your real name,

19:29.001 --> 19:31.845
but I have a new mission now,
protecting these kids!

19:32.004 --> 19:33.631
Soos, you idiot,
let me go!

19:33.839 --> 19:34.806
(grunts)

19:35.841 --> 19:36.888
<i>Let me go!
C' men!</i>

19:37.093 --> 19:38.640
Mabel, press
the red button!

19:38.803 --> 19:41.431
- Shut it down!
- No, you can't! You gotta trust me!

19:41.639 --> 19:46.486
Grunkle Stan, I don't even know
if you're my Grunkle!

19:46.686 --> 19:48.313
I wanna believe you,
but--

19:48.479 --> 19:50.026
Then listen to me.
Remember this morning,

19:50.231 --> 19:53.075
when I said I wanted
to tell you guys something?

19:53.275 --> 19:54.697
COMPUTER: T-minus 20 seconds.
ALL: ( yelling )

19:57.822 --> 20:00.621
I wanted to say that you're gonna hear
some bad things about me,

20:00.825 --> 20:04.079
and some of 'em are true, but trust
me, everything I've worked for,

20:04.245 --> 20:06.998
everything I care about,
it's all for this family.

20:07.164 --> 20:08.837
Mabel,
what if he's lying?

20:08.999 --> 20:11.593
This thing could destroy
the universe! Listen to your head!

20:11.794 --> 20:13.171
STAN: Look into my eyes, Mabel!

20:13.379 --> 20:14.847
You really think
I'm a bad guy?

20:15.047 --> 20:17.891
He's lying!
Shut it down, now!

20:18.092 --> 20:18.809
STAN: Mabel, please!

20:19.009 --> 20:20.352
COMPUTER: Ten, nine...

20:24.974 --> 20:25.896
Grunkle Stan...

20:26.100 --> 20:27.522
COMPUTER: Six, five...

20:29.937 --> 20:32.110
I trust you.

20:32.314 --> 20:34.408
Mabel, are you crazy?!
We're all gonna--

20:34.608 --> 20:35.734
COMPUTER: One.

20:37.862 --> 20:38.909
[[511

20:39.113 --> 20:39.909
Aah!

20:40.114 --> 20:40.910
Aah!

20:41.115 --> 20:42.037
Aah!

21:17.943 --> 21:20.571
W-what?
Who is that?

21:20.780 --> 21:22.623
The author
of the journals.

21:24.408 --> 21:26.877
STAN: My brother!

21:27.077 --> 21:28.875
Is this the part
where one of us faints?

21:29.079 --> 21:33.676
Oh, I am so on it, dude.
